  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ComponentManager.OnAttachListener
    Callback invoked when a Component is attached to a host.
    ComponentManager.OnDetachListener
    Callback invoked when a Component is detached to a host.
    Config<E>
    Config is a small set-and-forget object meant to define configurations of objects such as GameObjectManager.GObjects and ImageComponents and apply such configurations when needed automatically.
    ControlMap
    A hub for input Events to be distributed when the appropriate hardware is triggered (an early control mapping system).
    CreateEventHandler
    Wrapper for an EventHandler of type CreateEvent.
    DestroyEventHandler
    Wrapper for an EventHandler of type DestroyEvent.
    EventDispatcher
    EventDispatcher registers EventHandlers and EventDispatcher.EventFilters to be notified of specific Events when the appropriate process(Event) methods are called.
    EventDispatcher.EventFilter<E extends Event>
    Decides whether or not a given Event is a desired target Event to be processed in an EventDispatcher.
    EventHandler<E extends Event>
    Handles Events submitted to the EventHub.

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Camera  
    CameraManager  
    ComponentManager  
    ComponentManager.Component
    Base class for all game object components to attach to a game object.
    ComponentPattern  
    ConcurrentConsoleInput<E>
    Access to console input without blocking the main thread.
    CreateEvent
    CreateEvents represent the creation of GameObjectManager.GObjects and subsequent placement in the game world.
    DebugCtrl
    Provides query and control to many services and functions such as creating GameObjectManager.GObjects and checking the current framerate.
    DefaultControlMap
    This ControlMap implementation assumes one KeyEvent and one MouseEvent is submitted per game tick.
    DefaultEventDispatcher
    Default EventDispatcher implementation used when no user implementation is provided.
    DefaultEventHub
    This EventHub implementation is used when no user implementation is provided.
    DestroyEvent
    DestroyEvents represent the destruction of specified GameObjectManager.GObjects.
    Event
    Base class for Events created and sent around the engine to notify and request.
    EventHub
    DefaultEventHub is a centralized depot for Events to be stored for later propagation.
    Game<T>
    This class is responsible for not only controlling the game's tick rate but also providing properties and services to different parts of the game.
    Game.Resources<E extends GameObjectManager.GObject>
    The Resources class provides access to various factories which produce not only ComponentManager.Components for assembling GameObjectManager.GObjects but also other sources for building game materials such as the GObjectFactory itself.
    Game.Services
    Services gives access to parts of the engine that control specific aspects such as user control bindings or handling and publishing Events.
    GameObjectManager  
    GObjectFactory
    GObjectFactory is responsible for producing GameObjectManager.GObjects to act as whatever game object is needed.
    InputEvent
    Describes the InputEvent.Action input that forms a common basis for a KeyEvent and MouseEvent by describing each InputEvent with an Action such as InputEvent.Action.PRESS or InputEvent.Action.RELEASE.
    KeyEvent
    KeyEvents represent InputEvents generated by keyboard interaction and are described by the KeyEvent.Key that performed the InputEvent.Action.
    MeshManager  
    MeshManagerTest  
    MouseEvent
    MouseEvents represent InputEvents generated by mouse interaction and are described by the MouseEvent.Button that performed the InputEvent.Action as well as the screen coordinates of the cursor at the time of the action.
    ViewManager  
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    InputEvent.Action
    Constants describing an InputEvent's nature: either a press, release, repeat, scroll forward, or scroll backward.
    KeyEvent.Key
    Keyboard key constants for describing KeyEvents.
    MouseEvent.Button
    Mouse button constants for describing MouseEvents.
